==English==

===Etymology===
First attested [[w:1482|1482]], from {{MF.}} [[adolescent]], from {{L.}} [[adolescentem]], [[nominative]] form of [[adolescens]], [[past participle]] of [[adolescere]], "to [[grow up]]," from [[ad-]], "[[to]]" + [[alescere]], "to [[grow]] or be [[nourished]]." The adjective first appeared in [[w:1785|1785]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|ăd′l-ĕsənt}}

===Adjective===
'''adolescent'''
#Characteristic of, or relating to, or undergoing [[adolescence]]; immature.

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[nuori]]
*Portuguese: [[adolescente]] ''m'' and ''f''
*Telugu: [[కౌమార]] (kaumaara)
* French : adolescent

===Noun===
#A [[teenager]]; a [[juvenile]] after [[puberty]]

====Translations====
